eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge reports from Nkandla. Courtesy of #DStv403 NKANDLA - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala was also at Nkandla on Saturday. Zikalala told the crowd of Zuma supporters that the way forward is being discussed. READ: Zikalala: We stand with Zuma On Tuesday, the Constitutional Court ordered the former president be imprisoned for 15 months for contempt of court. He had ignored its order to testify at the State Capture Inquiry. READ: Zuma maintains his innocence The court has now agreed to hear Zuma's application to have the order against him rescinded. Zikalala said, "it is clear that the society is divided. We are engaging with all stakeholders. Will engage internally and see how we go forward. The fact that is now in the Constitutional Court makes us able to solve the matter where it should be."